<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="687" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d687">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 867.48/811</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Agent and Consul General at Cairo</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gary</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-06">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 6, 1918</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your 23, March 30. In view of banking conditions Department will continue
                            to transmit relief funds through Agency for payment to and distribution
                            by the commission authorized by British Government, you paying proceeds
                            of drafts to their agent at Cairo.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>